## Deployment architecture

| Component | Service name | Port | Bridge / path |
|---|---|---|---|
| WordPress Docker | `panhandle-wp` | 8090 | `panhandle_blueprint.py` -> `http://127.0.0.1:8090`, prefix `/demos/panhandle-garage-door-company` |
| SEO Analyzer backend | already in Flask | n/a | `/auth/register`, `/auth/login`, `/seo/analyze` тАФ no new blueprint |

Port 8090 confirmed available (only registered port is 3742 for orschell; Maryland WP was 8081).

**WP Docker compose:**
```yaml
services:
  wordpress:
    image: wordpress:6.6
    ports: ["8090:80"]
    environment:
      WORDPRESS_DB_HOST: db
      WORDPRESS_DB_NAME: panhandle
      WORDPRESS_DB_USER: wp
      WORDPRESS_DB_PASSWORD: panhandle_wp_2026
  db:
    image: mysql:8.0
    environment:
      MYSQL_DATABASE: panhandle
      MYSQL_USER: wp
      MYSQL_PASSWORD: panhandle_wp_2026
      MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD: panhandle_root_2026
    volumes: ["panhandle_db:/var/lib/mysql"]
volumes:
  panhandle_db:
```

**Bridge blueprint:** Clone `maryland_driveway_wp_bridge_blueprint.py`, change:
- `PREFIX = "demos/panhandle-garage-door-company"`
- `UPSTREAM = "http://127.0.0.1:8090"`
- Blueprint var/name: `panhandle_wp_bridge_bp`
- All 3 WP login filters + `redirect_canonical` suppression + Host/X-Forwarded-Proto + no-redirect opener + strip `accept-encoding` тАФ copy verbatim from Maryland blueprint.

**Service registration:** `surface_register_service.py` with `NAME=panhandle-wp`. Docker image pull is large тАФ register as service so `run-server.ps1` owns startup. Do NOT block in `/run/exec`.

**Demo admin credentials (document in build report):**
- WP admin URL: `https://api.michaelwegter.com/demos/panhandle-garage-door-company/wp-admin/`
- Username: `admin` | Password: `DimitroffAdmin2026!`
- SEO analyzer: any fake email + min-8-char password

