## Requirement-to-feature traceability

| Requirement | Implemented as |
|---|---|
| WordPress migration from Squarespace | Custom WP theme on Docker; Redirection plugin for 301s |
| Mobile-first, fast loading, Core Web Vitals | Minimal theme, no page builder, WP Super Cache, lazy WebP images |
| SEO-focused site architecture | Content silos (/services/, /commercial/, /residential/) + hub-and-spoke LPs |
| Schema markup | LocalBusiness + Service + FAQPage + BreadcrumbList on all pages |
| XML sitemap / robots.txt | Yoast SEO plugin |
| Individual city landing pages | 12 city LPs (9 TX + 3 NM) from scalable `page-city.php` template |
| Individual service pages | 8 service pages + 2 hubs from `page-service.php` template |
| Commercial service pages | Dedicated `/commercial/` hub + commercial angle in 3+ city LPs |
| Educational content/blog | `/blog/` hub + 1 full sample post |
| GSC / GA / conversion tracking | Setup guide in WP admin; CF7 thank-you redirect for goal tracking |
| Increase qualified phone calls | Click-to-call in sticky header + mobile footer bar + in-page CTAs |
| Scale to dozens of SEO landing pages | Template architecture тАФ add a page, assign `page-city.php`, fill ACF or custom meta |
| Open-signup SEO analyzer | Existing `api.michaelwegter.com/auth/register` + GH Pages analyzer app |
| Docs/training | `training-docs.md` as WP sticky admin page + `/estimate/` form |
| Bilingual differentiator | "Se Habla Espa├▒ol" in trust strip + every city LP + footer |

